 full-stack real-time chat application built with React, Node.js, Express, Socket.IO, and styled using Tailwind CSS. Users can send and receive live chat messages instantly.

🚀 Features
🔌 Real-time bi-directional messaging with WebSockets (Socket.IO)

🧠 Global chat context using React's Context API

🎨 Clean UI with Tailwind CSS

📁 Well-structured backend and frontend folders

🌐 Client-server communication through WebSocket events

🛠️ Tech Stack
Frontend:

React

Tailwind CSS

Context API + useEffect/useState

Socket.IO-client

Backend:

Node.js

Express.js

Socket.IO-server

CORS

📁 Project Structure
bash
Copy
Edit
/client
  ├── public/
  ├── src/
  │   ├── components/     # Chat UI components
  │   ├── context/        # React Context for global state
  │   ├── socket/         # Socket.io-client setup
  │   └── App.jsx
/server
  ├── index.js            # Express and Socket.IO setup
  └── package.json
⚙️ Getting Started
1. Clone the Repo
bash
Copy
Edit
git clone https://github.com/your-username/realtime-chat-app.git
cd realtime-chat-app
2. Install Dependencies
📦 Server
bash
Copy
Edit
cd server
npm install
📦 Client
bash
Copy
Edit
cd client
npm install
3. Run the App
▶️ Start Backend (Port: 4000)
bash
Copy
Edit
cd server
npm run dev
▶️ Start Frontend (Port: 5173 by default)
bash
Copy
Edit
cd client
npm run dev
Make sure both the client and server are running.

🧪 Testing
Open two browser windows/tabs at http://localhost:5173

Send messages from one and see them appear instantly on the other.

🌍 Deployment Tips
Use services like Render, Railway, or [Vercel + Cyclic combo] for free deployments.

Enable CORS correctly on server for deployed frontend domain.

Replace localhost with your production server URL in socket.js.

